Representatives from government and industry will discuss:
- What you need to know to do business with government -- electronically
and cost effectively
- Steps to implementing an effective EDI program
- Financial EDI initiatives and the benefits to government
- How to make that all-important business link between the public and
private sectors
- How to make you existing EDI program more effective
- Getting your EDI system under control
- EDI and CALS

CONFERENCE HIGHLIGHTS
The conference this year has been organized into concurrent sessions
dedicated to a thorough discussionof subjects of major importance to
electronic commerce as the technology that will help to reinvent
government. The speakers have been selected based on their experience,
dedication and commitment to expanding electronic commerce in the public
and private sectors.

PRE-CONFERENCE MANAGEMENT BRIEFINGS
These pre-conference management briefings will be presented as tutorials
on September 12, 1994.

Learn why electronic commerce has been made a top priority of the Clinton
Administration -- and how this has already begun to impact doing business
with the government!

- EDI -- The Basic Concepts
- EDI -- Control Concepts
- Re-engineering -- How to Benefit

POST-CONFERENCE TECHNICAL WORKSHOPS
These post-conference workshops on September 15, 1994 will cover:
- Client/Server -- Overview, Benefits, Pitfalls and Perspectives
- Total Quality Management
- EDI and Government Imaging

EXHIBITOR SHOWCASE
See the latest in software, supplies and services. Hours are Tuesday,
September 13, 10:00 a.m.-5:30 p.m. and Wednesday, September 14, 10:00-
5:00 p.m. There will also be a reception on Tuesday from 4:00 to 5:30
p.m. in the Exhibit Hall.

